Bionomics. A number of hoverfly species have been recorded as a host (See
Yu et al . 2016
for detail). In Japan , the following seven species have been recorded as a host:
Betasyrphus serarius (Wiedemann, 1830)
;
Episyrphus balteatus (De Geer, 1776)
;
Eupeodes (Metasyrphus) corollae (Fabricius, 1749)
,
Eupeodes frequens Matsumura, 1917
;
Ischiodon scutellaris (Fabricius, 1805)
;
Meliscaeva omogensis (Shiraki & Edashige, 1953)
;
Platycheirus urakawensis (Matsumura, 1919)
( Uchida, 1957 ; Minamikawa, 1969 ; Kusigemati, 1981 ).
